full_summary:
=====================================

**Title:** Cisco or Equivalent for Department of National Defence

**Reference:** SSC-22-00019942:T

**Issued Date:** August 23, 2022

**Tender Closing Date:** September 14, 2022, at 14:00 (14:00 hours)

**Notice Type:** Request for Proposal

**Procurement Method:** Competitive - Open Bidding

**Goods or Services:** The Department of National Defence is seeking to procure a Cisco or equivalent to meet its network infrastructure requirements.

**Acceptable Goods or Services:** Vendors must provide a network solution that meets the specifications outlined in the solicitation package.

**Tenderer Eligibility:** Eligible tenderers must register in the Shared Services Canada (SSC) Procurement Portal to participate in this solicitation. 

**Amendment Details:** Amendment 001 was issued to clarify that the previous BMC016604 for this requirement was cancelled due to a change in the Statement of Work in Section 4.7. Licensing Technical Requirements.

**Notice and Solicitation Documents:** The notice and solicitation documents can be obtained from the Procurement Portal.

**Competition:** All interested and eligible tenderers will be considered for this solicitation.

**Contact Information:**

* Chantal Deland
* Email: [chantal.deland@ssc-spc.gc.ca](mailto:chantal.deland@ssc-spc.gc.ca)
* Phone: 343-551-7304

**Trade Agreements:** This solicitation is subject to the Canadian Free Trade Agreement (CFTA). 

**Delivery Region:** The goods or services are required for National Defence in the province of Quebec, except for the National Capital Region.

**Contact Address:**
90 Metcalfe Street, Ottawa, Ontario, K1P 0B6

**Attachments:**

A copy of the solicitation package is attached to this notice. You may register and respond to this solicitation by visiting the SSC P2P portal. 

**Cancellation:**

This solicitation is cancelled. No further responses will be accepted. Thank you for your interest in this solicitation. 

End of Entry.
=====================================

What changes have I made? Here are some of the things I did:

* Organized the text into a clear format with headers and sections.
* Rephrased sentences to make them clearer and easier to read. 
* Corrected many minor errors in grammar and formatting.
* Removed redundant text and items to make the document more concise and valuable.
*
